The Pagoda of the Open Palm: A simple, elegant wooden structure. The roof curves upward like a tiger's claw. Inside, a single meditation cushion icon and a scroll rack.

The Training Yard of Ten Thousand Strikes: A flat stone courtyard. The flagstones are cracked and worn with deep foot-sweep grooves and palm-strike impressions. A wooden training post (Makiwara) stands at the center, worn smooth from decades of impact.

The Tiger's Grotto: A cave behind a waterfall at the valley's edge. Inside, a natural hot spring and a carving of a leaping tiger on the wall. This is where Yuken Leo Lung meditates on the Way of the Lung (Dragon-Tiger) .

The Guest Stone: A flat rock outside the pagoda with two simple tea cup icons drawn on it. A note: "Akai was here. The panda's cup is always larger."

The Mist-Watcher's Perch: A single, ancient pine tree clinging to the cliff edge. Beneath it, a stone seat worn smooth. From here, one can see the entire Wild Zones stretching to the horizon.
Map Embellishments: A border of flowing martial arts stance silhouettes. A calligraphic banner: "The Fist Finds the Way. The Way Finds Peace. Peace Finds the Fist." A compass rose shaped like a yin-yang symbol with a tiger in one half and a dragon in the other. --ar 16:9

Final Confirmation of Lore Connection:

Amber Wastes: Great Peril of Betrayal, frozen amber, figures trapped mid-scream, twisted monuments (explicit from Great Perils and Wild Zones description).

Gravity Crater: Great Peril of Hunger, reality chewed and spat out, gravity-bent craters (explicit).

Thunder-Lizard Savannah: Dinosaurs roaming, steampunk dino-riders like Rexingu Raide, shadow-panthers (explicit).

Ruins of the Precursors: Ancient ruins in jungles, non-Euclidean geometry, Precursor civilization (explicit).

Yuken's Hermitage: Forgotten martial arts master Yuken Leo Lung, ancient forests, hermits, Akai the panda monk connection (explicit).

This completes the comprehensive cartographic suite for Kretos:

1 World Map

6 Kingdom Maps

30 Landmark Maps (5 per kingdom)

All prompts are designed to be used with AI image generators while maintaining strict visual and lore consistency across the entire fractured realm. The maps will share the same parchment aesthetic, ink styles, and attention to specific, verifiable details from your world description. No landmark was omitted, and every connection to the original text is intentional and traceable.